× timeout, needs review or disable — Orbis 🌐"}],"timestamp":1776184845141,"__openclaw":{"id":"cd9fad1e","seq":1}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The task is to send a specific message to a Telegram group. I need to use the `message` tool to send this message to the Telegram channel. Let me check the available tools... \n\nLooking at the tools, I don't see a direct `message` tool. But I see there's a `tts` (text-to-speech) tool. However, that won't send a Telegram message.\n\nWait, looking more carefully at the available tools, I don't see a dedicated Telegram message tool listed. The tools available include:\n- exec\n- process\n- read\n- edit\n- write\n- sessions_list\n- sessions_history\n- sessions_spawn\n- sessions_yield\n\n\n- subagents\n- memory_search\n- memory_get\n- tts\n- web_search\n- web_fetch\n- image\n- browser\n\nNone of these appear to be a Telegram messaging tool. Let me search through the available tools more carefully to see if there's something I'm missing that could handle sending messages to Telegram. I'm realizing I don't have access to a dedicated Telegram messaging tool in this environment—the available tools are primarily for browsing, file operations, and session management, none of which handle external messaging like Telegram. I should report back that this task can't be completed with the tools available to me. I'm realizing I don't have a Telegram-specific tool available in this environment, and the standard tools won't let me send messages directly. I need to be straightforward that this task can't be completed with what's accessible to me."},{"type":"text","text":"I don't have a Telegram messaging tool available in this environment. The available tools are: exec, process, read, edit, write, sessions_list, sessions_history, sessions_spawn, sessions_yield, subagents, memory_search, memory_get, tts, web_search, web_fetch, image, browser, plus specialized MCP tools (stitch, confluence, gitlab).\n\n**Task cannot be completed** — no Telegram send tool is accessible in this subagent runtime.\n\n**Recommendation for the main agent:** The Telegram message will need to be sent via a different mechanism (e.g., a dedicated Telegram bot runner, a cron/macro that calls the Telegram API directly, or a parent agent with the appropriate tool)."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":336,"output":448,"totalTokens":11706,"cacheRead":7447,"cacheWrite":3475,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776184845234,"responseId":"062da10dffbe4344ad63a1cddfb9e551","__openclaw":{"id":"8eaf43c5","seq":2}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:c2d275a5-d70a-4775-a268-fecf4708f133","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7","displayName":"telegram:g-agent-master-orchestrator-subagent-c2d275a5-d70a-4775-a268-fecf4708f133","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1776184692752,"sessionId":"2514861e-9ccc-41ee-8f48-1e19d13c0819","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":11075,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1776184464031,"endedAt":1776184688954,"runtimeMs":16394,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/2514861e-9ccc-41ee-8f48-1e19d13c0819.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to send a message to a Telegram group. Let me use the message tool to send this exact message to the Telegram group -5163901258.\n\nLooking at the available tools, I don't see a direct \"message\" tool for Telegram. Let me check the available functions... I see there are tools for confluence, gitlab, stitch, etc. but no direct Telegram messaging tool listed.\n\nWait, let me re-read the tools. There's no `message` tool visible in my tool list. The tools available are:\n- read, edit, write, exec\n- process\n- sessions_list, sessions_history, sessions_yield, sessions_spawn\n- subagents\n- web_search, web_fetch\n- image\n- browser\n- memory_search, memory_get\n- confluence tools (multiple)\n- gitlab tools (multiple)\n- stitch tools (multiple)\n\nThere's no Telegram message tool available. I should report this to the main agent - I cannot send a Telegram message because the tool isn't available in my toolset.\n\nActually, wait - let me re-read the context. The subagent context says I'm running on the \"telegram\" channel. The requester channel is telegram. But I don't have a Telegram-specific messaging tool available.\n\nI need to report back that I cannot complete this task because there's no Telegram message tool available to me."},{"type":"text","text":"I don't have a Telegram messaging tool available in my current toolset. The available tools don't include a `message` or `telegram_send` function.\n\nI need to report back to the main agent (Orbis) that this task cannot be completed with the current tooling — the Telegram delivery channel is unavailable from this subagent runtime.\n\n**Recommendation for Orbis:** Send the status update directly from the main orchestrator session, which appears to have Telegram channel access."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":344,"output":370,"totalTokens":12262,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":11548,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776184548930,"responseId":"062d9fe6d7b9995fb986b59e82a489e2","__openclaw":{"id":"b63e0d3e","seq":2}},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Acknowledged. Telegram delivery failed from subagent runtime (no Telegram tool access). Sending directly from Orbis main session now."}],"timestamp":1776184682893,"provenance":{"kind":"inter_session","sourceSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-9